    <briefdescription>
<para>Sleep coordinator — low-power mode management. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Coordinates sleep entry with the scheduler. When all tasks are idle (or only timer-blocked), the system can enter a low-power mode. Clients can veto sleep by holding a &quot;stay awake&quot; lock.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Architecture</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Each subsystem that needs the CPU awake holds a lock.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>When all locks are released, the scheduler calls <ref refid="syn__sleep_8h_1ac38c1db283b2121d7ec1189904ec85d4" kindref="member">syn_sleep_enter()</ref> which invokes the port sleep function.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Interrupts wake the MCU, and the scheduler resumes.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structSYN__Sleep" kindref="compound">SYN_Sleep</ref><sp/>sleep;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__sleep_8h_1a2a356bbd8431290ba3964aba05de9a57" kindref="member">syn_sleep_init</ref>(&amp;sleep,<sp/><ref refid="syn__sleep_8h_1a3982260032578bb148402b075c84941aaf3f2ece414ff6be26e4775fdd1018d4a" kindref="member">SYN_SLEEP_LIGHT</ref>);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>UART<sp/>ISR:<sp/>hold<sp/>lock<sp/>while<sp/>transmitting</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__sleep_8h_1a349e1d982abc198d59e5ef8fcc14deaf" kindref="member">syn_sleep_lock</ref>(&amp;sleep,<sp/><ref refid="syn__sleep_8h_1a4db5634481ffc78b3cdbd812e8d7e5a6" kindref="member">SYN_SLEEP_LOCK_UART</ref>);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>...<sp/>transmit<sp/>complete<sp/>...</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__sleep_8h_1a088c01b66ed2d03f1f51965dccdd1fc9" kindref="member">syn_sleep_unlock</ref>(&amp;sleep,<sp/><ref refid="syn__sleep_8h_1a4db5634481ffc78b3cdbd812e8d7e5a6" kindref="member">SYN_SLEEP_LOCK_UART</ref>);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>In<sp/>scheduler<sp/>idle<sp/>hook:</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__sleep_8h_1ac38c1db283b2121d7ec1189904ec85d4" kindref="member">syn_sleep_enter</ref>(&amp;sleep);<sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>sleeps<sp/>only<sp/>if<sp/>no<sp/>locks<sp/>held</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
